During a press briefing, Surgeon General Vivek Murthy discussed the urgent public health crisis of health misinformation, particularly in relation to COVID-19. He emphasized that health misinformation spreads rapidly in the digital age, with social media platforms enabling the dissemination of false and misleading information. Murthy issued a Surgeon General's Advisory on the dangers of health misinformation and outlined recommendations for individuals, health organizations, educational institutions, researchers, foundations, technology companies, and news organizations to combat misinformation. He highlighted the importance of accurate information in making informed decisions about health and the potential harm caused by health misinformation, including avoidable illnesses and deaths. Murthy also shared his personal experience of losing family members to COVID-19 and emphasized the need for everyone to confront misinformation and take responsibility in the fight against it.